---
import Site from '../layouts/Site.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---
<Site
  title="About — Neil Busque"
  description="Who Neil Busque is: an independent operator and builder. Digital marketing, SEO, paid search, AI agents, automations, and web apps, shipped fast and in public."
  canonical="https://busqueneil.com/about"
  active="about"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <Breadcrumb items={[
      { name: 'Home', url: 'https://busqueneil.com/' },
      { name: 'About', url: 'https://busqueneil.com/about' },
    ]} />
  </Fragment>

  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><span class="idx">∗</span> About</p>
    <h1>Operator who <span class="accent">builds</span>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">New Jersey. I turn marketing into running systems, and I ship the work in public.</p>
  </header>

  <article class="article-page" style="padding-top: 8px;">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm Neil Busque. I work at the seam between marketing and engineering:
        digital marketing, SEO, and paid search on one side; funnels, CRM,
        automation, AI agents, and custom web apps on the other. The throughline
        is the same: turn spend and ideas into systems that actually run.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days I build, independently and fast. Web apps, PWAs, AI agents,
        CRM systems, automations. Most of it ships within days of the idea, and
        all of it gets posted to <a href="/">the feed</a> as it happens. This
        site is my playground and my public notebook. Before New Jersey it was
        Korea, and before that the Philippines.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm open to full-time roles in digital marketing, SEO, paid search, and
        marketing operations, and to project work. The fastest way to reach me is
        <a href="mailto:busqueneil@gmail.com">busqueneil@gmail.com</a>, or
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/neilbusque" rel="me">LinkedIn</a>.
        There's a <a href="/resume.pdf">resume</a> if you want the formal version.
      </p>
      <p>
        Need help with something specific? I run two small offers:
        <a href="/help/">pay-what-it-was-worth consulting</a> and
        <a href="/build/">custom app builds</a>.
      </p>
      <h2>Outside the work</h2>
      <p>
        Mornings start with devotion. I lift on alternate days, keep a few books
        going at once, and build apps and AI agents for fun, which looks a lot
        like the day job. The best part of any day is a call with my wife, who is
        still in the Philippines. The goal is simple: bring her and our cat,
        Hiro, home to the US. Until then I travel back as often as I can.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Site>
